	<text>
		<body>
				<p><addressee>Revd. Mr. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>London</placeName> <date>22 June 5614</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">In due course I received your<lb/> favor of <date>16<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> Ulto with an order on <persName>Mr Joel<add>&#63;</add></persName> for &#163;1.12.<lb/> which has been paid &#38; is to your credit&#44; but I cannot<lb/> admit it as amt. of the 4 copies that you state are<lb/> sold for you had no authority to sell there for less<lb/> than 9&#47; for me &#38; that was allowing you 20pct as the<lb/> price they were sent to you at 12&#47; The price they sell at<lb/> here.  Whoever told you <persName>Mr. Abraham</persName> sold them &#64; 8&#47;<lb/> must have told you a falsehood for that Gent<hi rend="sup">n</hi>. would<lb/> not sell them &#64; 8&#47; &#38; remit me 10&#47; for every one he sold<lb/> The copy sent you was as I wrote at the time for<lb/> the purpose of review&#44; which was never done&#44; as to<lb/> your advertising it that was for your own benefit<lb/> for you were to have 3&#47; out of the 12&#47;.  You say you have<lb/> lost by my business which I cannot understand&#44; but to<lb/> prevent any further loss to you&#44; please send back the<lb/> copies unsold &#38; an order for the balance due me &#38; thus<lb/> close a business which has been far from pleasant or<lb/> profitable to yours &#38;c</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">EHLindo</persName></p>
		</body>
